name: Z2 Georg Thiele
acquisitionMethod: Limited in Light Construction, Drops in SP3 in event "Star of the Shining Fjord"

1.name: Default
1.description: Type 1934 class Destroyer - Z2 Georg Thiele

limitBreak.tier1: Gains Full Barrage I / Torpedo Efficiency +5%
limitBreak.tier2: Max Torpedo Capacity +1 / Pre-loaded Torpedo +1 / Torpedo Efficiency +10%
limitBreak.tier3: Upgrades Full Barrage I→II / All Weapon Efficiency +5%

2.name: Combat Improvement
2.description: Every 10 times the main battery is fired, increase Reload by 1.5% (5%), Full Barrage damage is increased by 20% (40%), and stacks up to 4 times.

3.name: Full Barrage I-II
3.description: Every 15 (10) times the main battery is fired, trigger Full Barrage - Z-class I (II)

1.chinese: 1934型驱逐舰—Z2 格奥尔格·蒂勒
1.japanese: 1934型駆逐艦・Z2ゲオルク・ティーレ

2.chinese: 格奥尔格·蒂勒，代号Z2，作为1934年型实验性的驱逐舰诞生，运用高超的机动性玩弄对手，本应该是这样的……没什么，当我没说过好
2.chineseTL: Georg Thiele - Codename Z02. I'm an experimental destroyer who uses my high speed to destroy the enemy. Or at least that's how it's supposed to be... Never mind, pretend I never said that.
2.japanese: ゲオルク・ティーレ、またの名をZ2、実験的に建造された1934型の駆逐艦です。優れた機動力で相手を翻弄するはずだったのですが……なんでもありません。今のは聞かなかったことにしてください
2.japaneseTL: I'm Georg Thiele, also known as Z2, one of the experimentally built Type 1934-class destroyers. I was supposed to toy with the enemy through superior mobility, but... it's nothing. Please pretend you didn't hear this just now.

3.chinese: Z2，格奥尔格·蒂勒，听从您的命令。不过，要是您的命令有误，还请让我考虑一下。
3.chineseTL: Z2, Georg Thiele. I will obey. However, please allow me to reconsider questionable orders.
3.japanese: Z2（ゲオルク・ティーレ）です。ご命令を。ええ、ですが命令に不備があったら、考えさせてください。よろしくお願いします
3.japaneseTL: I'm Z2 (Georg Thiele). Your orders, please. However, if there are any deficiencies with the orders, please let me reconsider them. I'll be in your care.

4.chinese: 指挥官，我有一个疑问，为什么您每次都来的比我晚？
4.chineseTL: Kommandant, why do you always arrive later than me?
4.japanese: 指揮官、なぜいつもわたしより遅く来るのですか？と、一つ質問です。
4.japaneseTL: A question. Commander, why do you always arrive after me?

5.chinese: 指挥官，我有一个疑问，不停地给大家换上不同的武装，对您来说，难道是一种爱好吗？
5.chineseTL: Kommandant, if I may ask you a question - ceaselessly swapping everyone's equipment.. could it be a hobby of yours?
5.japanese: 指揮官、みんなに色んな服を着せ替えるのは趣味ですか？と、一つ質問です
5.japaneseTL: A question. Commander, is making everyone wear various outfits your hobby?

6.chinese: 指挥官，如果可以的话，请不要像Z1那样随便暴走，打晕会很麻烦，而且我也不想随便向上级出手
6.chineseTL: Kommandant, please stop running around like Z1. It'll troublesome to subdue you, and I don't wish to raise my hand against a superior.
6.japanese: 指揮官、できればレーベくんみたいに暴れたりはしないでください。気絶させるのは面倒くさいですし、上官に手を出すのは本望ではありません。はい
6.japaneseTL: Commander, if you could, please don't act wildly like Lebe-kun. Knocking you out would be a pain, and I wouldn't enjoy laying my hands on my superior.

7.chinese: 您要是很闲的话，我就把接下来的报告书全都搬过来了，请做好心理准备
7.chineseTL: Kommandant. If you are bored, I have bought over reports. Please prepare yourself.
7.japanese: 暇でしたら、ええ、書類を全部持ってきますので、ご覚悟ください
7.japaneseTL: If you're free, then, please prepare yourself, I'll bring all the documents.

8.chinese: 我手里的这孩子叫Z1，是的，您没有听错，它就叫Z1，很可爱对吧？
8.chineseTL: The child in my hands? Its name is Z1. That's right. It's called Z1. It's cute, right?
8.japanese: この子の名はレーベくんです。ええ、聞き間違いではありません、レーベくんです。可愛いですね
8.japaneseTL: This child's name is Lebe-kun. Yes, you didn't hear wrong, Lebe-kun. Cute, right?

9.chinese: 嗯，是，没错，您说得对，那么还有什么事吗？
9.chineseTL: Umu. Yes. That's correct. What you say is true. Now, is there anything else?
9.japanese: はい、もちろん、仰る通りです。ほかに用件は…？
9.japaneseTL: Yes, of course, it is as you said. Is there anything else...?

10.chinese: 指挥官，在表现勇气的方式里，我认为这是最差的一种
10.chineseTL: Kommandant.. I feel like this is the most tasteless way to showcase your bravery.
10.japanese: 勇気のある行動の中でも最低な部類だと思います。ええ
10.japaneseTL: Amidst all the ways to express your courage, this is the lowest possible one in my opinion. Yes.

11.chinese: 有新的任务，指挥官，我已经用浅显易懂的方式整理好了
11.chineseTL: New missions. Kommandant, I have already arranged them neatly.
11.japanese: 新しい任務です。わかりやすく取りまとめました。ええ
11.japaneseTL: A new task. I've arranged it in an easy to understand manner. Yes.

12.chinese: 虽然要我代为接收任务奖励也可以，但是那样的话，我心中对指挥官的评价会降低的，您确定吗？
12.chineseTL: Though I may accept the reward for completing the mission, my opinion of the commandant will fall. Are you sure?
12.japanese: 任務報酬を受け取るのは構いませんが、私の指揮官への評価は下がります。よろしいでしょうか
12.japaneseTL: Even though it is not a problem for me to go receive the mission rewards, my opinion of the Commander will go down. Is it okay?

13.chinese: 信件，根据我对指挥官您的了解，建议立刻拆阅，不然的话很可能会忘记
13.chineseTL: New letters. According to my understanding of the Commander, I would advise that you open them immediately, lest you forget.
13.japanese: メールです。はい、すぐにでも開封して確認することをおすすめします。でないと、指揮官のことですから、すぐに忘れてしまいますので。はい
13.japaneseTL: Mail. Yes, I recommend opening it immediately. Knowing you, Commander, if you don't, you'll forget about it. Yes.

14.chinese: 遵照您的命令，我已经清点了这次的战果报告，请过目
14.chineseTL: As per your orders, I have checked the combat report. Please look it over too.
14.japanese: 命令通り、戦果報告を取りまとめました。ご確認を
14.japaneseTL: As per your orders, I've compiled the combat report. Please review it.

15.chinese: 委托组归来，根据规定，您应该去关照一下，当然如果需要的话，我会与您一同前往。
15.chineseTL: The fleet is returning. As per regulations, you're required to observe. Of course, if needed, I will accompany you.
15.japanese: 委託組が帰還しました。出迎えて、彼女たちを労うのが道理でしょう。…必要でしたらわたしもご一緒します
15.japaneseTL: The commission team has returned. When greeting them, it would make sense to show them appreciation, no? ...If it is required, I will accompany you.

16.chinese: 再变强下去，就不会拥有缺陷了吗？
16.chineseTL: If I get stronger, will I lose my defects?
16.japanese: これ以上強化されたら、欠陥も出てくるのではないのでしょうか…？
16.japaneseTL: If I am enchanced further, surely no flaws will appear...?

17.chineseTL: Don't rush ahead - beware of ambushes.
17.japanese: 待ち伏せに注意。前に出過ぎないように……
17.japaneseTL: Carefully lie in ambush. Don't rush ahead...

18.chinese: 请不要放松警惕，因为一次胜利后的大意而最终失败的战局…比比皆是
18.chineseTL: Please don't let down your guards. There have been many examples of defeat that followed a victory.
18.japanese: 勝利に浮かれたのち負けてしまう事例は数え切れません。警戒を怠らないよう、お願いします
18.japaneseTL: Please remain on your guard. There are many examples of suffering defeat while celebrating one's victory.

19.chinese: 我来殿后吧，请放心，托Z1的福，我很擅长这种事
19.chineseTL: I'm retreating. Please don't worry, I have become quite accustomed to it - thanks to Z1's luck.
19.japanese: しんがり、やります。レーベくんのおかげで得意です。こういうの。安心してください
19.japaneseTL: I'll be the rear guard. Thanks to Lebe-kun, I'm pretty good at this. Please rermain calm.

20.japanese: 早くなれる。もう少しだけ
20.japaneseTL: I'll become faster. Just a bit more

21.chineseTL: The front turret's taking water.. this doesn't bode well.
21.japanese: 砲塔浸水……まずいです。ええ
21.japaneseTL: The turret is flooding...this is bad. Yes.

22.chinese: 我就算了，请您尽量离Z1远一点
22.chineseTL: I give up, please keep your distance from Z1.
22.japanese: わたしはいいですが、レーベくんから離れていただきたいです。はい
22.japaneseTL: Even though I am fine with this, please leave Lebe-kun alone. Yes.

23.chinese: 指挥官，来找我是想知道Z1的事吗？……我的？唔，这个要求还真是稀奇，请让我考虑一下
23.chineseTL: Kommandant, did you wish to know more about Z1? ...Me? That's a strange request. Please allow me some time to consider.
23.japanese: 指揮官、レーベくんについて何か知りたいのですか？…わたしのことを知りたい、ですか？珍しいこともありますね。ええ、少し考えさせてください
23.japaneseTL: Commander, do you want to know about Lebe-kun? ...want to know about me? How unusual. Let me tell you a bit then.

24.chinese: 指挥官，又来找我聊天吗，想必您已经对我有所了解，我可不会为了顾及您的感受而说好话哦？还是说，您其实很享受这种感觉？
24.chineseTL: Kommandant, are you here for a chat again? As you understand, I won't mince my words. Or perhaps.. you enjoy that?
24.japanese: また雑談ですか。わたしのことを知っていれば、相槌以上の返事がされないことは自明の理だというのに？それともこの味気ないセリフを楽しんでいるのでしょうか？
24.japaneseTL: You want to chat again? Even though, knowing me, you know you won't receive more than interjections in return? Or could it be that you enjoy such dull exchanges?

25.chinese: 您的想法虽然经常异于常人，什么拯救世界，让大家都获得幸福之类的。不过对接受过Z1洗礼的我来说，和您这样的人相处说不定才刚刚好呢
25.chineseTL: Though what is on your mind is different from ordinary people, what with saving the world and global happiness.. But as someone who has received Z1's baptism, you might be the perfect fit.
25.japanese: 変わった考えをたくさん持ってる指揮官ですが、レーベくんに振り回されてきたわたしにとって、指揮官のようなタイプこそちょうどいいのかもしれません。ええ
25.japaneseTL: Although you're brimming with unusual ideas, Commander, perhaps someone like you is perfect for me, who has been thrown around by Lebe-kun. Yes.

26.chinese: 指挥官，如果您希望和我的关系更进一步的话，我建议您不要做多余的蠢事，就像平常一样，做您想做的事，说您想说的话，那样就很好
26.chineseTL: Kommandant, you don't have to do anything special if you wish to take our relationship one step further. Keep doing the things you do, speak your mind and be yourself.
26.japanese: 指揮官、わたしとの関係を更に進展させたいのでしたら、普段どおり――そのまま言いたいことを言い、やりたいことをやってください。それで十分です。ええ
26.japaneseTL: Commander, if you wish to further develop your relationship with me, just do as you normally do - say what you wish to say, do what you wish to do. That is enough. Yes.

27.chinese: 原来如此，这就是契约，这就是和某个人建立起了牢不可破的关系的感觉……咦，您说我脸红了？……能不能请您帮我拍一张照，我还没见过自己脸红的样子
27.chineseTL: So this is the pledge.. This what people feel when they make an unbreakable promise. Oh... I'm blushing? Please take a picture, for I have never seen myself blush.
27.japanese: これがケッコンですね。揺るぎないつながりを持つようになったこの気持ち……わたしの顔が赤くなっている、ですか？……すみません、今のわたしの顔を撮っていただけないでしょうか。赤くなった自分の顔、見たことがありませんので。ええ
27.japaneseTL: So this is marriage. The feeling of creating an unbreakable bond... my face has become red, you say? ...could you please take a photo of me? I have never seen myself blushing before. Yes.

29.chinese: Z1，注意点，帮你善后很麻烦的
29.chineseTL: Z1, please be careful. It's troublesome to take care of you.
29.japanese: レーベくん、気をつけて、後始末は面倒くさいですから
29.japaneseTL: Lebe-kun, be careful, cleaning up after you is bothersome.

30.chinese: 让我们乘风破浪……算了，学不来
30.chineseTL: Let us ride the waves .. never mind, nothing can be learnt from this.
30.japanese: 風に乗って波を……やはり無理ですね。ええ
30.japaneseTL: Riding the wind and waves... is impossible after all, huh. Yes.
